package wandemptyproofblock

// Regression test for the `{ ... }` predicate-constructor syntax: a magic wand whose
// `package` statement has an empty proof block, e.g.
//
//     package P() --* P() {}
//
// used to be misparsed. The empty `{}` was greedily consumed as (empty) predicate-constructor
// arguments applied to the wand's right-hand side `P()` (i.e. `P(){}`), which then failed during
// translation with "Wrong base type for predicate constructor". The `{}` must instead be
// recognized as the `package` statement's (empty) proof block. This also happens when the wand is
// parenthesized, `package (P() --* P()) {}`.

pred P()

requires P()
func bare() {
	package P() --* P() {}
}

requires P()
func parenthesized() {
	package (P() --* P()) {}
}
